author: realbigsean
content:
Thanks! It looks the new transactions root is correct! I got a step closer to proposing but now I am getting an error from my local execution engine when validating the payload:

`ExecutionPayloadError(RejectedByExecutionEngine { status: InvalidBlockHash { validation_error: None } })`

So I think there might be an issue with how `blockHash` is being calculated: 

https://github.com/ethereum/execution-apis/blob/main/src/engine/specification.md#specification

```
Client software MUST validate blockHash value as being equivalent to Keccak256(RLP(ExecutionBlockHeader)), where ExecutionBlockHeader is the execution layer block header (the former PoW block header structure). Fields of this object are set to the corresponding payload values and constant values according to the Block structure section of EIP-3675, extended with the corresponding section of EIP-4399.
```
